message.content: cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE. This paper deals with improving a Recurrent Neural Network for question answering, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). The use of NLP techniques such as noun chunking and entity detection suggest that this paper is likely to be categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The focus on hyper-parameter tuning and improving model accuracy also suggests a connection to machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely category as well. The use of the SimpleQuestions dataset and the focus on accuracy in relation prediction suggest a connection to information retrieval, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible category. Finally, the use of neural networks and the focus on improving model performance suggest a connection to neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible category as well.
